<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>622</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002D</addr>  <route>axt-002D.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional continuous basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>intensional continuous basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> with the further requirement that
  for every <tex>x : D</tex>, the directed <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex>  given by the basis satisfies the condition
  <tex display="block">\forall  k : K_x. \  \beta ( \kappa _x(k))  \ll  x.</tex></p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>623</anchor>   <addr>axt-002M</addr>  <route>axt-002M.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author> </authors> <title>Terminology for domain theory</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  In <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">Tom de Jong</link>'s <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">thesis</link> and his Agda formalization of domain
  theory, the term ‚Äústructurally continuous‚Äù is used to mean a
  <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> equipped with a function giving, for every <tex>x :
  D</tex>, a small directed family of elements way below <tex>x</tex>, giving <tex>x</tex> as its
  join.
</p><p>  In the new terminology, this notion of ‚Äústructure‚Äù involved in the continuity
  of a dcpo is made explicit by the following notion.
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>624</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002H</addr>  <route>axt-002H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Continuity datum for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <em>continuity datum</em> for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is a function
  giving, for every <tex>x : D</tex>, a specified <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,
   \kappa _x)</tex> on <tex>D</tex> satisfying the following conditions.
  <ol>    <li>The family <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> is directed.</li>    <li><tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }_{k : K_x}  \kappa _x(k)</tex>.</li>    <li>For each <tex>k : K_x</tex>, <tex>\kappa _x(k)  \ll  x</tex>.</li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree><p>  Factoring this structure out into a definition of its own obviates the need to
  have a name for the notion of a ‚Äú<tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo having a specified continuity
  datum‚Äù, which is what ‚Äústructurally continuous‚Äù means. Even though the
  equivalence between <link href="axt-0027.xml" type="local" title="Unintentionally left blank">structurally continuous</link> and ‚Äúhaving a
  specified <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link>‚Äù is completely trivial, we still record
  this in the following proposition to be able to explicitly refer to this
  terminological identity.
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>2</crumb></trail> <anchor>625</anchor>  <taxon>Proposition</taxon> <addr>axt-001K</addr>  <route>axt-001K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>24</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author> </authors>  <meta name="source"><b>Defn 4.4.1</b> of <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">de Jong</link>'s <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">PhD thesis</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> having a specified <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link>  is the same thing as <tex>D</tex> being <link href="axt-0027.xml" type="local" title="Unintentionally left blank">structurally continuous</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><p>  By replacing the specified existence here with mere existence, we obtain the
  notion of a <link href="axt-002I.xml" type="local" title="Continuous V-dcpo">continuous <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link>. The terminology for this is
  unchanged (i.e. is the same as the terminology of <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">Tom de Jong</link>'s
  <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">thesis</link>).
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>3</crumb></trail> <anchor>626</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002I</addr>  <route>axt-002I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Continuous <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> is called <em>continuous</em> if there exists a
  <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link> for it.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>4</crumb></trail> <anchor>627</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0029</addr>  <route>axt-0029.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Pseudocontinuous <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> is called <b>pseudocontinuous</b> if there is
  a specified function giving, for every <tex>x : D</tex>, the mere existence of a
  <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> on <tex>D</tex> satisfying the following
  conditions.
  <ul>    <li>The family <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> is directed.</li>    <li><tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }_{k : K_x}  \kappa _x(k)</tex>.</li>    <li>For each <tex>k : K_x</tex>, <tex>\kappa _x(k)  \ll  x</tex>.</li>  </ul></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>5</crumb></trail> <anchor>628</anchor>  <taxon>Remark</taxon> <addr>axt-0031</addr>  <route>axt-0031.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> being pseudocontinuous is the same thing as it
  having a specified <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link>, but with the specified
  existence requirement in the notion of <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link> relaxed to
  requirement of mere existence.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>6</crumb></trail> <anchor>629</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002D</addr>  <route>axt-002D.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional continuous basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>intensional continuous basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> with the further requirement that
  for every <tex>x : D</tex>, the directed <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex>  given by the basis satisfies the condition
  <tex display="block">\forall  k : K_x. \  \beta ( \kappa _x(k))  \ll  x.</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>7</crumb></trail> <anchor>630</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002E</addr>  <route>axt-002E.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Extensional continuous basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>extensional continuous basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-002D.xml" type="local" title="Intensional continuous basis for a V-dcpo">intensional continuous basis</link> that is <link href="axt-0028.xml" type="local" title="Extensional basis for a V-dcpo">extensional</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>8</crumb></trail> <anchor>631</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002B</addr>  <route>axt-002B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Algebraicity datum for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>algebraicity datum</em> for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is a function
  giving, for every <tex>x : D</tex>, a specified <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link>  <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> on <tex>D</tex> that satisfies the following.
  <ol>    <li>The family <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> is directed.</li>    <li><tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }_{k : K_x}  \kappa _x(k)</tex>.</li>    <li>For each <tex>k : K_x</tex>, <tex>\kappa _x(k)</tex> is compact.</li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree><p>  Similar to the case of a <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link>, we record the
  terminological identity between a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> being
  <link href="axt-001C.xml" type="local" title="Structural algebraicity of a dcpo">‚Äústructurally algebraic‚Äù</link> (the terminology from <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">de
  Jong</link>'s <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">thesis</link>) and it having a specified
  <link href="axt-002B.xml" type="local" title="Algebraicity datum for a V-dcpo">algebraicity datum</link>.
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>9</crumb></trail> <anchor>632</anchor>  <taxon>Proposition</taxon> <addr>axt-002A</addr>  <route>axt-002A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> having a specified <link href="axt-002B.xml" type="local" title="Algebraicity datum for a V-dcpo">algebraicity
  datum</link> is the same thing as <tex>D</tex> being <link href="axt-001C.xml" type="local" title="Structural algebraicity of a dcpo">structurally
  algebraic</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>10</crumb></trail> <anchor>633</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001L</addr>  <route>axt-001L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>24</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Algebraic <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is called <em>algebraic</em> if there exists an
  <link href="axt-002B.xml" type="local" title="Algebraicity datum for a V-dcpo">algebraicity datum</link> for it.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>11</crumb></trail> <anchor>634</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002C</addr>  <route>axt-002C.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Algebraic <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> (alternative)</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>D</tex> be a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> and define the type
  <tex display="block">K_x   \vcentcolon \equiv   \sum _{c : D}{ \mathsf{isCompact} ( c )   \times  c  \sqsubseteq  x}</tex> of
  compact elements below a given <tex>x : D</tex>. The <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is
  called <em>algebraic</em> if it satisfies the following conditions.
  <ul>    <li>For every <tex>x : D</tex>, <tex>K_x</tex> is <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-small.</li>    <li>The <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \mathsf{pr} _1 )</tex> is directed with supremum <tex>x</tex>.</li>  </ul></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>12</crumb></trail> <anchor>635</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002F</addr>  <route>axt-002F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional algebraic basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>intensional algebraic basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional
  basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> satisfying
  <tex display="block">\forall  b : B. \  \mathsf{isCompact} ( \beta (b) ) .</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>13</crumb></trail> <anchor>636</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002G</addr>  <route>axt-002G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Extensional algebraic basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>extensional algebraic basis</em> for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-002F.xml" type="local" title="Intensional algebraic basis for a V-dcpo">intensional algebraic basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> that is
  <link href="axt-0028.xml" type="local" title="Extensional basis for a V-dcpo">extensional</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>637</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0022</addr>  <route>axt-0022.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>D</tex> be a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link>. An <em>intensional basis for <tex>D</tex></em> is a
  <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> on <tex>D</tex> satisfying the condition: for every
  element <tex>x : D</tex>, there is a specified directed <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link>  <tex>(I_x,  \iota _x)</tex> on the basis index <tex>B</tex> such that
  <tex>x =  \bigvee  (I_x,  \beta   \circ   \iota _x).</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>638</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001F</addr>  <route>axt-001F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author>Ayberk Tosun</author> </authors> <title>ùì•-Family</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <em><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family on a type <tex>A :  \mathcal{U}</tex></em> is a pair <tex>(I,  \iota )</tex> where
  <ul>    <li><tex>I</tex> is a type in universe <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>,</li>    <li>and <tex>\iota</tex> is a function of type <tex>I  \to  A</tex>.</li>  </ul></p><p>  List of formal definitions:
  <ol>    <li>      <link href="https://www.cs.bham.ac.uk//~mhe/TypeTopology/Slice.Family.html#262" type="external">Fam in UF.Slice</link>      in TypeTopology.
    </li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>639</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002E</addr>  <route>axt-002E.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Extensional continuous basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>extensional continuous basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-002D.xml" type="local" title="Intensional continuous basis for a V-dcpo">intensional continuous basis</link> that is <link href="axt-0028.xml" type="local" title="Extensional basis for a V-dcpo">extensional</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>